Center Parcs Logo
For over 50 years Center Parcs has been the place to make new memories with your loved ones. Fully equipped cottages in the midst of nature, our subtropical swimming paradise Aqua Mundo, the indoor tropical Market Dome and a huge range of indoor and outdoor activities makes Center Parcs the ideal place for an unforgettable holiday. And no matter how diverse our offer, it’s all in the service of that one, universal need: togetherness.

 New York City Department of Parks and Recreation Logo
The New York City Department of Parks and Recreation, also called the Parks Department or NYC Parks, is the department of the government of New York City responsible for maintaining the city’s parks system, preserving and maintaining the ecological diversity of the city’s natural areas, and furnishing recreational opportunities for city’s residents and visitors.
